'''September 6''' is the 6th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/September (Lunisolar)|qq=}}  the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}  day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|qq=}} .

== Events ==
* [[:en:Hōki|Hōki (era)]]  1 ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]]  [[:en:770|770]]  [[:en:September 29|September 29]] ) – [[:en:Wake no Kiyomaro|Wake no Kiyomaro]] , who had been exiled to [[:en:Ōsumi Province|Ōsumi Province]] , is recalled to the capital following the death of [[:en:Empress Kōken|Empress Shōtoku]]  and the downfall of [[:en:Dōkyō|Dōkyō]] .
* [[:en:Bunka|Bunka (era)]]  1 ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  [[:en:1804|1804]]  [[:en:October 9|October 9]] ) – Russian envoy [[:en:Nikolai Rezanov|Nikolai Rezanov]] , representing Emperor {{ill|Alexander I of Russia|ja|アレクサンドル1世 (ロシアEmperor)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Alexander I of Russia|qq=}} , arrives in Nagasaki to request trade relations.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Kansei|ja|Kansei|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kansei|qq=}}  3 ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  [[:en:1791|1791]]  [[:en:October 3|October 3]] ) – {{ill|Matsudaira Naritsune|ja|松平斉恒|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Naritsune|qq=}} , 8th lord of the [[:en:Matsue Domain|Matsue Domain]]  (+ [[:en:1822|1822]] ).

== Deaths ==
* [[:en:Kennin|Kennin (era)]]  3 ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]]  [[:en:1203|1203]]  [[:en:October 12|October 12]] ) – [[:en:Nitta Tadatsune|Nitta Tadatsune]] , a samurai general (* [[:en:1168|1168]] ).
* [[:en:Eishō (Muromachi period)|Eishō (Muromachi period)]]  15 ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]]  [[:en:1518|1518]]  [[:en:October 10|October 10]] ) – {{ill|Amago Masahisa|ja|尼子政久|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amago Masahisa|qq=}} , a samurai general (* [[:en:1488|1488]]  or [[:en:1494|1494]] ).
* [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]]  1 ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  [[:en:1624|1624]]  [[:en:October 17|October 17]] ) – [[:en:Kōdai-in|Kōdai-in]]  (also known as {{ill|Kita no Mandokoro|ja|北政所|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kita no Mandokoro|qq=}} , {{ill|One (Toyotomi)|ja|おね|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/One (Toyotomi)|qq=}} , or {{ill|Nene (Toyotomi)|ja|寧々|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nene (Toyotomi)|qq=}} ), wife of [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]]  (* [[:en:1548|1548]] ).
* [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]]  2 ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  [[:en:1705|1705]]  [[:en:October 23|October 23]] ) – {{ill|Matsudaira Yoshiyuki|ja|松平吉透|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsudaira Yoshiyuki|qq=}} , lord of the [[:en:Matsue Domain|Matsue Domain]]  (* [[:en:1668|1668]] ).
* [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]]  5 ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]]  [[:en:1858|1858]]  [[:en:October 12|October 12]] ) – [[:en:Hiroshige|Utagawa Hiroshige]] , a ukiyo‐e painter (* [[:en:1797|1797]] ).

